cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for neural architecture search for multimodal learning, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method in terms of performance and human intervention, which falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with multimodal learning, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
